Package fr.uga.jandas

Class DataFrame

java.lang.Object
fr.uga.jandas.DataFrame
public class DataFrame extends Object
The Dataframe class represents a 2-dimensions array where each column is identified by a label and each line by an index. Two different columns can host two different types.

The Dataframe class includes methods for examinating individual or multiple elements of the array. Moreover there are functions that providing statistics on columns.

Below the actual file format attend to create a Dataframe from a file. Input file format with n the number of column and m the number of line :
t0,t1,...,tn
l0,l1,...,ln
e00,e01,...,e0n
e10,e11,...,e1n
...,...,...,...
em0,em1,...,emn
The first line gives the type of each column. The second line gives the labels of each column. The following lines give the elements (data) to add in the DataFrame. Each cell is separated by a coma without space. Columns are stored thanks to Column class, and each Column can store objects sharing the same type.

    • createFrom

      public DataFrame createFrom(String[] labels)
      Returns a new Dataframe initialized given a column set of current Dataframe. Note that this is a deep copy, there are new objects used in this newly created DataFrame. Moreover, it can be many times the same label in the given column set. Returns null a label is unknown.
      Parameters:
      labels - The columns label to add in the new DataFrame.
      Returns:
      The newly created DataFrame or null.

    • createFrom

      public DataFrame createFrom(int[] indexes)
      Returns a new Dataframe initialized given a line set of current DataFrame. It uses function createPartialCopy() from the class Column on each column, a function that returns a deep copy with only specified lines. Note that this is a deep copy, there are new objects used in this newly created DataFrame. Returns null if an index is out of range.
      Parameters:
      indexes - The indexes set to add in the new DataFrame.
      Returns:
      The newly created DataFrame or null.

    • createFrom

      public DataFrame createFrom(String[] labels, int[] lines)
      Returns a new DataFrame initialized given a line and column set of current DataFrame. Only lines of indexes referenced in parameter are present in obtained columns. Note that this is a deep copy, there are new objects used in this newly created DataFrame. Returns null if an index is out of range or a labels is unknown.
      Parameters:
      labels - The columns label to add in the new DataFrame.
      lines - The indexes set to add in the new DataFrame.
      Returns:
      The newly created Dataframe based on the given selection and projection or null.
